WEBVTT

02:18.706 --> 02:20.440
Hi, Mom it's Josh.

02:21.509 --> 02:23.778
Obviously, got your message.

02:24.812 --> 02:26.614
Just been practicing.

02:28.348 --> 02:30.450
I know, surprise, right?

02:30.484 --> 02:34.522
Um, anyway, the piece
is really shaping up.

02:34.555 --> 02:35.923
Can't wait to play it for you.

02:35.957 --> 02:37.424
I can't really get there

02:37.457 --> 02:39.861
before morning, so hopefully it
can wait.

02:39.894 --> 02:42.630
Um, okay, see you for breakfast.

02:43.564 --> 02:44.532
Love you.

02:59.881 --> 03:01.582
- Good morning, Charlotte.
- Morning.

03:01.616 --> 03:03.951
- Where are you going now?
- Just going.

03:03.985 --> 03:05.687
- You're always going.
- What can I say?

03:05.720 --> 03:06.954
I'm busy.

03:11.993 --> 03:14.294
Happy birthday, Grandma.

03:14.327 --> 03:15.763
- Coconut chocolate?
- Of course.

03:15.797 --> 03:16.664
Oh!

03:17.364 --> 03:19.433
When are you going to
sit down and practice?

03:19.466 --> 03:20.868
You're welcome.

03:20.902 --> 03:22.436
Thank you, dear.

03:22.469 --> 03:23.838
When are you going to practice?

03:23.871 --> 03:25.338
January.

03:25.372 --> 03:26.974
Show me your hands.

03:28.810 --> 03:32.547
These fingers have not touched
the piano.

03:32.580 --> 03:33.480
- All up here.
- Oh!

03:33.514 --> 03:35.850
All up here.

03:35.883 --> 03:39.787
Internet is ruining your work
ethic, everything is too easy.

03:39.821 --> 03:41.823
It is Grandma, especially
that pest, YouTube,

03:41.856 --> 03:43.558
filling our brains with
infinite amounts of information.

03:43.591 --> 03:45.526
I'm surprised you have
any brain left at all.

03:45.560 --> 03:46.894
Grandma, why are you on my
case?

03:49.731 --> 03:51.899
Got it, I promise.

03:51.933 --> 03:53.735
Go, prove it to me.

04:15.056 --> 04:17.558
It's tomorrow, yes?

04:17.592 --> 04:19.493
Whatever happens, happens.

04:19.527 --> 04:21.394
Up against some tough pianists.

04:21.428 --> 04:23.798
That's never stopped you
before.

04:23.831 --> 04:26.934
Back in my day, we just made
music.

04:26.968 --> 04:29.036
We didn't have to compete to
earn a living for ourselves.

04:29.070 --> 04:30.004
I know, I know.

04:30.037 --> 04:32.807
"Competition's are for
horses not artists."

04:32.840 --> 04:35.843
- Who said that?
- Your grandpa.

04:35.877 --> 04:37.945
But Bartok said at first,

04:39.947 --> 04:42.817
If you are going to have to
compete to earn your supper,

04:42.850 --> 04:44.619
you've got to commit.

04:46.486 --> 04:49.023
You will be up against
kids that eat, drink,

04:49.056 --> 04:52.794
and sleep with Bach,
Beethoven and Horowitz.

04:52.827 --> 04:54.796
- Grandma.
- Laugh all you want,

04:54.829 --> 04:58.733
but I know that Victor Zabov
has a new favorite to win.

04:58.766 --> 05:01.869
Uh, Jake or Josh or something.

05:01.903 --> 05:05.706
A favorite, it's not a horse
race.

05:05.740 --> 05:07.108
And what do you mean, you heard?

05:07.141 --> 05:09.510
My musical school is a
hot topic at bridge club?

05:09.544 --> 05:11.879
This is serious, believe me.

05:11.913 --> 05:13.981
Zabov knows all the tricks.

05:14.015 --> 05:16.483
Please, if there was
someone of that caliber,

05:16.517 --> 05:18.519
- I'd know about him.
- You can't just

05:18.553 --> 05:21.022
float through this one.

05:21.055 --> 05:22.990
I don't think I'm going to
compete.

05:23.024 --> 05:24.759
Yes you are.

05:24.792 --> 05:26.359
And besides, if I'm there
too long then who's gonna

05:26.393 --> 05:28.996
- take care of you?
- You don't worry about me.

05:29.030 --> 05:31.498
You just get yourself ready.

05:32.200 --> 05:33.868
I've never asked you for
anything,

05:33.901 --> 05:37.038
but I am asking you to
take this one seriously.

05:37.071 --> 05:40.107
- Grandma, don't get all-
- Charlotte,

05:40.141 --> 05:42.910
I've got to know you'll
be okay after I die.

05:42.944 --> 05:45.445
- Grandma, stop.
- I've got to know.

05:45.478 --> 05:46.914
I need to know.

05:46.948 --> 05:48.381
It's just the competition.

05:48.415 --> 05:50.885
We both know that's not true.

06:08.169 --> 06:11.105
You remind me of your mother.

06:11.138 --> 06:14.474
Naturally gifted, incredibly
stubborn.

06:17.612 --> 06:21.582
You're going to win that
competition tomorrow.

06:21.616 --> 06:23.416
And she'd be so proud.

07:52.640 --> 07:55.576
Yeah, it was, I'll give you
that.

07:57.078 --> 07:59.213
- When am I gonna see you?
- Oh, gosh, soon.

07:59.246 --> 08:00.214
- I'm here.
- Yeah?

08:00.247 --> 08:01.582
- I'm here.
- All right.

08:01.615 --> 08:02.950
I'm back.

08:04.285 --> 08:05.920
- Mm!
- So good to see you.

08:05.953 --> 08:09.489
- Good to see you.
- It's good to be back.

08:12.660 --> 08:13.527
Hey, Josh!

08:14.695 --> 08:15.930
Josh, wait up!

08:17.932 --> 08:18.799
Josh!

08:24.805 --> 08:26.273
What do you want?

08:27.975 --> 08:30.644
Just a moment to talk with my
son.

08:30.678 --> 08:33.014
You're 20 years too late.

08:33.047 --> 08:35.783
I know, but I'm back for good,
I swear.

08:35.816 --> 08:36.884
I'm here for good.

08:36.917 --> 08:39.120
I can't deal with this right
now.

08:39.153 --> 08:40.821
Josh, Josh, stop!

08:53.367 --> 08:54.235
Thank you.

08:56.237 --> 08:57.104
Thank you.

08:58.806 --> 09:01.776
Your mom tells me about the
competition.

09:01.809 --> 09:04.311
She says every pianist who's won

09:04.345 --> 09:07.648
goes on to have lucrative
careers.

09:07.681 --> 09:09.283
That's exciting.

09:09.316 --> 09:10.851
I'm proud of you.

09:12.053 --> 09:17.224
Hey, you know, it would mean
a lot to me if you'd come by.

09:17.491 --> 09:22.063
It's no big London
competition, but it's a start.

09:22.096 --> 09:24.298
For me to be here for good.

09:27.668 --> 09:31.806
You would name an entire
gallery after yourself.

09:47.922 --> 09:49.957
Good morning, Barbara.

09:49.990 --> 09:52.126
How you doing, you look well
today.

09:52.159 --> 09:54.261
Uh, thank you, your
mom's in the kitchen.

09:54.295 --> 09:55.262
Thanks.

09:57.698 --> 10:02.203
Ew, boy, when was the
last time you showered?

10:02.236 --> 10:05.306
You can't keep a schedule like
this without getting sick.

10:05.339 --> 10:09.276
You need sleep and food that
doesn't come from a paper bag.

10:09.310 --> 10:11.045
Why do you give him the time
of day?

10:11.078 --> 10:12.713
How did he even know where to
find you?

10:12.746 --> 10:13.681
- Josh.
- And you're okay with that?

10:13.714 --> 10:15.349
You can just pick up
right where you left off

10:15.382 --> 10:17.985
whenever he feels like showing
up?

10:18.018 --> 10:20.688
There are things you
don't understand yet.

10:20.721 --> 10:22.723
And I don't like what's
been happening to you.

10:22.756 --> 10:24.725
You're in the practice room day
and night.

10:24.758 --> 10:25.960
It's not healthy.

10:25.993 --> 10:30.998
Look at you, how many hours
a week are you working now?

10:31.332 --> 10:32.800
I do it for you.

10:33.535 --> 10:36.270
I'm going to make things better
for you.

10:36.303 --> 10:39.106
He's your father, you need
him.

10:41.809 --> 10:44.111
I forgot, look what I have.

10:45.045 --> 10:48.115
And it's not your
job to take care of me.

10:48.149 --> 10:49.016
Mom.

10:50.117 --> 10:52.286
A real Broadway show!

10:52.319 --> 10:54.288
Uh, touring, but yeah.

10:57.258 --> 10:59.460
People change, Josh.

10:59.493 --> 11:02.429
Take Barbara, you know, it'll
be fun.

11:02.463 --> 11:04.231
You're coming, right?

11:04.265 --> 11:05.933
I have to work tonight.

11:05.966 --> 11:10.104
Not to his thing,
tomorrow, the competition.

11:10.137 --> 11:12.139
- I have to work, sweetie.
- Okay, my point exactly.

11:12.173 --> 11:15.042
I don't like how much
you're working lately.

11:15.075 --> 11:17.044
I keep telling you, I could get
a job.

11:17.077 --> 11:18.145
It might be nice change.

11:18.179 --> 11:20.481
We're not gonna get into this
again.

11:20.515 --> 11:23.017
Getting through school is your
job,

11:23.050 --> 11:25.986
putting you through school is
mine.

11:26.020 --> 11:28.923
So many rich people go to that
school.

11:28.956 --> 11:31.859
And maybe I could find you
some new clients, you know?

11:31.892 --> 11:33.360
One of them would equal three
Barbaras.

11:33.394 --> 11:35.062
Watch your mouth!

11:35.996 --> 11:40.401
Those people don't need me,
the Barbaras of the world do.

11:40.434 --> 11:42.770
I'm going to win for us.

11:44.905 --> 11:47.975
Come say hi to
Barbara.

11:48.008 --> 11:50.010
Mm, I need to get back to
practice.

11:50.044 --> 11:53.847
Boy, you better get
in there and say hello.

11:55.849 --> 11:57.985
So I understand you're leaving
us.

11:58.018 --> 11:59.987
Hope so, especially now.

12:00.020 --> 12:03.991
Well, you win and you
get to see the whole world.

12:04.024 --> 12:05.426
And take your mom with you.

12:05.459 --> 12:06.961
Yes, that's the point.

12:06.994 --> 12:09.096
Stop, both of you.

12:09.129 --> 12:11.265
If I win, you're coming with
me.

12:11.298 --> 12:14.536
Otherwise, all my hard work
will have been for nothing.

12:14.569 --> 12:16.504
Am I doing mom-guilt properly?

12:16.538 --> 12:18.405
Yes, very well done.

12:18.439 --> 12:19.206
Hmm.

12:19.240 --> 12:21.842
Did you see your father
earlier?

12:21.875 --> 12:25.145
Barbara, how did you know
that was Josh's father?

12:25.179 --> 12:27.114
I'm old, not dumb.

12:27.147 --> 12:29.283
They are the spitting
image of one another.

12:29.316 --> 12:30.818
Yeah, well looks are
all we have in common.

12:30.851 --> 12:31.519
Josh!

12:35.222 --> 12:38.292
Take a shower and go to bed.

12:38.325 --> 12:40.794
All right, peace and blessings.

12:40.828 --> 12:43.464
- Bye, Barbara.
- Good luck, Maestro.

12:56.143 --> 12:58.078
Is it too much to ask

12:58.879 --> 13:03.518
that one of you will be at
the piano when class begins?

13:03.551 --> 13:06.020
A little enthusiasm, people.

13:08.088 --> 13:09.557
Beatrice, Beatrice.

13:11.158 --> 13:12.527
Let's hear your Beethoven.

13:12.560 --> 13:15.162
Yes, Mr. Dempster, yes, sir.

13:58.673 --> 14:01.075
I think we've heard enough.

14:05.647 --> 14:08.382
You all have smartphones, right?

14:10.518 --> 14:14.088
I've been reading about apps
lately.

14:14.121 --> 14:16.023
I've heard they have one
were you can keep track

14:16.056 --> 14:18.593
of how many hours you practice.

14:18.626 --> 14:20.427
Um, would anyone like

14:21.161 --> 14:25.399
to volunteer to help me download
an app?

14:25.432 --> 14:26.300
You, sir.

14:27.535 --> 14:29.470
You can leave now.

14:29.504 --> 14:31.573
You seem so much more
enthusiastic

14:31.606 --> 14:35.442
about this technology
than you do the music.

14:35.476 --> 14:36.477
I'm serious!

14:38.646 --> 14:42.650
I don't have room in this
class for dilettantes!

14:46.420 --> 14:48.155
If any of the rest of you

14:48.188 --> 14:49.691
would rather play with your
phones,

14:49.724 --> 14:52.393
you're free to go with him!

14:52.426 --> 14:54.495
I don't care

14:54.529 --> 14:57.030
if you know how to download an
app!

14:57.064 --> 15:00.100
Just like I don't care if you
have

15:00.134 --> 15:01.669
rehearsals scheduled

15:01.703 --> 15:03.605
or classwork to do.

15:03.638 --> 15:07.642
And I particularly don't care,
if you have a social life!

15:07.675 --> 15:10.978
You're all here for one thing,
the music!

15:11.011 --> 15:13.615
Oh, and for those of you
that have been chosen

15:13.648 --> 15:16.116
for the final round of the
competition,

15:16.150 --> 15:17.519
the only thing you'll be doing

15:17.552 --> 15:20.454
between now and tomorrow is
practicing!

15:20.487 --> 15:23.257
You've never experienced this
kind

15:23.290 --> 15:26.260
of competition with these kinds
of stakes!

15:26.293 --> 15:28.162
Nerves will take over!

15:30.598 --> 15:34.468
London Prize only comes
around once every five years.

15:34.502 --> 15:37.739
So you won't get another shot!

15:37.772 --> 15:39.373
Josh, you're next.

16:25.152 --> 16:30.123
You think you're expressing
innocence, but it's not working.

16:32.527 --> 16:35.597
You need to play this
piece from the viewpoint

16:35.630 --> 16:39.734
of an old man, as though
he's remembering his youth.

16:39.767 --> 16:42.302
Listen to yourself, dig deep.

16:43.036 --> 16:47.107
Let me hear you as if
you were 70, understand?

16:48.743 --> 16:52.814
Now, go practice, you all
know what you need to do.

16:52.847 --> 16:56.316
It's been years to this point,
folks.

16:56.350 --> 16:59.286
And now it's tomorrow night.

16:59.319 --> 17:04.324
If you've made it this far,
you have what it takes to win.

17:04.526 --> 17:05.760
Although I'm starting

17:05.793 --> 17:08.395
to wonder if it's all a fluke.

17:13.801 --> 17:14.669
Come on.

17:29.617 --> 17:30.585
So now we're supposed

17:30.618 --> 17:34.254
to play from the point
of view of an old man.

17:34.288 --> 17:36.456
Sometimes I wonder if
we're in a music school

17:36.490 --> 17:39.326
or is this a real acting school.

17:41.395 --> 17:42.329
Charlotte.

17:46.701 --> 17:50.103
And you're the Josh
I've been hearing about.

17:50.137 --> 17:52.507
Don't worry, it's okay.

17:52.540 --> 17:55.510
Uh, I don't know who
you've been talking to.

17:55.543 --> 17:58.646
Well Zabov is crazy
about you, that's obvious.

18:00.815 --> 18:02.684
You look like you could use a
break.

18:02.717 --> 18:04.752
Wanna hang out, get out for a
while?

18:04.786 --> 18:06.386
Did you hear him?

18:06.420 --> 18:09.791
I can't go anywhere, shouldn't
you be practicing too?

18:09.824 --> 18:11.224
Even if you're not in the
competition,

18:11.258 --> 18:13.528
like Zabov expects it.

18:13.561 --> 18:16.698
Consider that a tip from one
of his most abused students.

18:16.731 --> 18:18.766
So you practice because he
tells you?

18:18.800 --> 18:20.668
I practice because I
wanna win the competition.

18:20.702 --> 18:22.570
I wanna have a career.

18:25.205 --> 18:29.911
So are you coming with me?

18:29.944 --> 18:32.346
You know, I could help you.

18:33.781 --> 18:35.783
- Help me?
- Yes.

19:03.611 --> 19:06.514
Tell you what, why not play
hooky for this afternoon?

19:06.547 --> 19:09.617
Or are you afraid Zabov will
catch you?

19:10.618 --> 19:11.886
You know how crazy things get
around here

19:11.919 --> 19:13.320
before a competition.

19:13.353 --> 19:14.622
That's called practicing.

19:14.656 --> 19:16.791
You see a guy standing on his
head

19:16.824 --> 19:19.226
while he practices, you know
you've been here for too long.

19:19.259 --> 19:20.293
What guy?

19:20.327 --> 19:21.763
You know when you see him,

19:21.796 --> 19:26.567
and when you do, you know
it's time to get out of here.

19:30.437 --> 19:34.307
Well, if you change your
mind, I'll be around.

19:38.345 --> 19:40.748
You know, you're not going
to find what it means

19:40.782 --> 19:42.416
- in the practice room.
- And what exactly...

19:46.854 --> 19:49.590
It's way too tethered,
do you understand?

19:50.892 --> 19:52.492
Ah, Joshua Irving.

19:53.493 --> 19:54.696
A word, please.

19:57.297 --> 19:58.866
What happened in class today?

19:58.900 --> 20:01.502
You seemed distracted.

20:01.536 --> 20:03.270
Nerves, I guess.

20:03.303 --> 20:06.941
If you win this competition,
you'll be in demand.

20:06.974 --> 20:11.946
They won't all be big concerts,
but concerts, nonetheless,

20:11.979 --> 20:14.549
college towns, small cities.

20:16.483 --> 20:18.485
Did you know that there are
people

20:18.519 --> 20:21.923
who don't want to see you
in this competition, Joshua?

20:21.956 --> 20:24.391
You have to want it.

20:24.424 --> 20:28.261
I gave up everything
important for my career.

20:28.295 --> 20:30.363
Are you ready to do that?

20:32.299 --> 20:36.704
And you've got to work twice
as hard because of who you are.

20:36.738 --> 20:37.939
Here you go.

20:37.972 --> 20:40.975
Two totally different
interpretations of your Beethoven.

20:41.008 --> 20:43.511
Listen, get some ideas.

20:43.544 --> 20:45.713
Hey oh, I'm sorry.

20:45.747 --> 20:46.914
I didn't know you had a student
in here.

20:46.948 --> 20:47.749
I'll come back.

20:47.782 --> 20:49.917
No, no, we're winding up right
now.

20:49.951 --> 20:51.018
This is Josh.

20:52.352 --> 20:53.755
He's in the finals tomorrow.

20:53.788 --> 20:55.857
That's quite an honor,
what piece have you chosen?

20:55.890 --> 20:58.325
- Uh, "Pathetique."
- Really?

20:58.358 --> 21:00.728
Well that's quite an intense
piece for a man so young.

21:00.762 --> 21:04.699
He handles it like a
man beyond his years.

21:04.732 --> 21:05.767
You'll never get another
chance

21:05.800 --> 21:07.702
like the one you have tomorrow.

21:07.735 --> 21:09.737
Victor, will I see you tonight?

21:09.771 --> 21:11.606
Ah, crowds aren't my thing.

21:19.013 --> 21:21.481
Uh, thanks for these.

21:21.516 --> 21:24.051
Josh, you may think I'm harsh,

21:25.953 --> 21:29.557
but out there are people
who will judge you harshly

21:29.590 --> 21:33.426
based on everything from your
technique to your skin color.

21:33.460 --> 21:35.696
You've got to be flawless.

21:35.730 --> 21:36.964
You've got to play so

21:36.998 --> 21:40.835
that they have no excuse not to
hire you.

21:40.868 --> 21:42.469
Do you understand?

21:45.540 --> 21:46.406
All right.

22:07.061 --> 22:09.396
Dude, get out!

23:27.074 --> 23:29.844
Hey, Mom, Um, I know you're at
work.

23:29.877 --> 23:33.714
I'm just here practicing,
probably for a few more hours

23:33.748 --> 23:35.016
and then I'm gonna head home
early.

23:35.049 --> 23:37.785
So call me if you need anything.

24:36.210 --> 24:38.779
Hey, your
mom gave me your number.

24:38.813 --> 24:42.149
Uh, said I should call.

24:42.183 --> 24:45.619
You know how convincing she can
be.

24:45.653 --> 24:50.057
Anyway I'm really hoping you'll
come to the opening tonight.

24:50.091 --> 24:52.226
It would mean a lot to me.

24:53.894 --> 24:56.697
I just wanna share this with
you.

25:12.780 --> 25:13.647
Saw him?

25:15.583 --> 25:18.819
Yeah, it's something like
that.

25:18.853 --> 25:20.721
I just needed a break.

25:23.824 --> 25:25.626
What's with the balloons?

25:25.659 --> 25:27.595
They're for my niece.

25:28.362 --> 25:30.131
You know, when I asked you to
hang out

25:30.164 --> 25:34.702
for a while, I mean, it was
longer than just a break.

25:35.636 --> 25:37.038
I have to be somewhere now.

25:37.071 --> 25:40.608
And we're gonna be there a
while.

25:40.641 --> 25:41.308
Why me?

25:42.710 --> 25:43.577
Why not?

25:48.182 --> 25:49.316
Coming or not?

25:58.125 --> 25:59.126
You got a car?

26:31.959 --> 26:34.695
Happy birthday, Amy.

26:34.728 --> 26:36.997
Kazoos, thanks, Aunt Char.

26:37.731 --> 26:41.268
Who are you, are you my aunt's
boyfriend?

26:41.302 --> 26:43.804
Daddy, who's that man?

26:43.838 --> 26:46.874
Well, I hope for his sake,
the balloon delivery man.

26:46.907 --> 26:49.410
- Daddy, you silly.
- Yeah.

26:49.443 --> 26:50.778
Cute, yours?

26:51.513 --> 26:54.882
So how did my sister rope you
into this?

26:54.915 --> 26:56.817
I volunteered.

