sister?

28:08.022 --> 28:09.290
Oh, we just...

28:10.291 --> 28:11.425
Not long.

28:11.458 --> 28:12.661
And do you play piano?

28:12.693 --> 28:17.198
Yeah, actually, apparently
we're at the same conservatory.

28:17.231 --> 28:19.033
"Apparently."

28:19.066 --> 28:22.369
We have a family full of
musicians.

28:22.403 --> 28:25.039
Um, Amy is just starting to take
lessons,

28:25.072 --> 28:26.807
and Milo plays cello.

28:26.840 --> 28:29.109
Though, not so much anymore.

28:29.143 --> 28:32.479
Um, are you competing
tomorrow in the London com...

28:34.949 --> 28:37.484
You like our song, Amy and
I are gonna start a band.

28:37.519 --> 28:39.320
- Oh.
- The Kazoo Keepers.

28:39.353 --> 28:40.321
You get it, you get it?

28:40.354 --> 28:43.824
It's very cute.

28:43.857 --> 28:46.260
So is Josh coming tonight?

28:46.293 --> 28:48.395
Is that within our schedule?

28:48.429 --> 28:50.164
Well, I have to go practice,
actually.

28:50.197 --> 28:51.533
So I don't think that's gonna
happen.

28:51.566 --> 28:55.302
Oh, you could take a
page out of his book, huh?

28:55.336 --> 28:56.870
See, Charlotte's so naturally
gifted,

28:56.904 --> 28:57.871
she takes things like
practicing.

28:57.905 --> 28:59.240
- We have to go.
- For granted.

28:59.273 --> 29:00.374
Look at that.

29:00.407 --> 29:02.343
- Here you go.
- Oh.

29:02.376 --> 29:04.144
But we haven't had cake yet.

29:08.282 --> 29:09.783
Poor kid.

29:13.887 --> 29:14.855
Cake!

29:17.057 --> 29:19.059
So where can I drop you?

29:19.093 --> 29:20.194
We had an understanding.

29:20.227 --> 29:21.996
You said you wouldn't weird out
on me.

29:22.029 --> 29:23.464
- Don't do that.
- Do what?

29:23.497 --> 29:26.300
You say like I said something
I didn't.

29:26.333 --> 29:30.170
Well, we're here now
and it's still early

29:30.204 --> 29:31.338
and I know you want to be alone

29:31.372 --> 29:33.307
and this competition is a big
deal

29:33.340 --> 29:35.142
to you, but I'm gonna be
late if I don't go now

29:35.175 --> 29:36.578
and it's on the way back

29:36.611 --> 29:39.113
to school and I promise
we're gonna go right back

29:39.146 --> 29:42.349
to school and I'll be out of
your hair.

29:44.418 --> 29:46.020
It's on the way?

29:50.858 --> 29:51.892
Okay.

30:18.586 --> 30:20.321
- This my friend Josh.
- Woo!

30:23.390 --> 30:25.326
Right, rock stars, button it
up.

30:25.359 --> 30:26.327
Wanna show Josh what we worked
on?

30:26.360 --> 30:27.494
- Yeah!
- Yeah.

30:30.364 --> 30:31.231
One, two.

31:38.566 --> 31:39.967
Woo, yeah!

31:40.000 --> 31:41.034
- Way to go!
- Yeah!

31:49.143 --> 31:50.712
You composed that?

31:50.745 --> 31:52.312
I mean, then they busted
out with that rock riff.

31:52.346 --> 31:54.214
I don't even understand
where that comes from.

31:54.248 --> 31:57.151
Like how, what made
you put that with jazz?

31:57.184 --> 31:58.620
I put things I like.

31:58.653 --> 32:01.989
Um, like what kind of
music do you listen to?

32:02.022 --> 32:05.058
- What do you mean?
- What's on your playlist?

32:05.092 --> 32:08.128
I don't know, Beethoven, Bach,
Mozart.

32:09.564 --> 32:13.100
What, what's on
yours?

32:13.133 --> 32:16.370
Led Zeppelin, John
Coltrane, Taylor Swift.

32:16.403 --> 32:17.605
Taylor Swift?

32:18.338 --> 32:20.240
You can't live in the
world doing the same thing

32:20.274 --> 32:23.076
over and over and expect to be
inspired.

32:23.110 --> 32:27.314
Besides, Taytay knows how
to get the party started.

32:29.183 --> 32:30.518
So why classical?

32:31.686 --> 32:34.087
What do you mean?

32:34.121 --> 32:37.191
Why are you studying classical
music, why did you pick it?

32:37.224 --> 32:38.959
I don't know, I...

32:41.161 --> 32:42.597
It picked me, I guess.

32:42.630 --> 32:47.635
I mean, I was around age six
when I started taking lessons.

32:48.202 --> 32:50.404
And it came easy in a way.

32:50.437 --> 32:53.675
You know, my anger just seemed
to flow right into the music.

32:53.708 --> 32:56.176
Why were you angry at six?

32:58.513 --> 33:01.381
Um, so what's the deal with
you and those kids anyway?

33:01.415 --> 33:02.684
Like, are you like a teacher?

33:02.717 --> 33:04.552
I volunteer there once a week.

33:04.586 --> 33:06.754
Music helped me when I was a
kid.

33:06.788 --> 33:11.258
Figure it was something small
I could do to bring back.

33:11.291 --> 33:12.694
Besides, it's fun.

33:14.796 --> 33:18.633
Speaking of ways to have fun,
how's working with Zabov?

33:18.666 --> 33:21.435
Huh!

33:21.468 --> 33:23.270
How long have you been with
him?

33:23.303 --> 33:25.339
- Four years.
- Oh my God.

33:25.372 --> 33:26.340
- Yeah.
- Ooh!

33:26.373 --> 33:28.208
Wanna hear something funny?

33:28.242 --> 33:29.209
Okay.

33:29.243 --> 33:32.346
My grandma and Zabov
used to have a thing.

33:32.379 --> 33:33.715
A thing?

33:33.748 --> 33:36.116
And it was serious,
apparently.

33:36.149 --> 33:37.585
She talks about him all the
time,

33:37.619 --> 33:39.821
but she would never admit that.

33:39.854 --> 33:41.723
I think it's hilarious.

33:41.756 --> 33:46.059
It's basically the reason why
I avoided studying with him.

33:46.093 --> 33:48.596
So how's that going anyway?

33:48.630 --> 33:51.431
What, your grandma and Zabov?

33:51.465 --> 33:52.734
You and Zabov.

33:52.767 --> 33:56.538
He's tough.

33:56.571 --> 33:58.105
I need that.

33:58.138 --> 33:59.206
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

33:59.239 --> 34:01.709
You know, like discipline.

34:03.845 --> 34:04.712
What?

34:05.880 --> 34:08.716
We've been in the same school,
both

34:08.750 --> 34:11.853
about to graduate, and yet
I have never ever seen you.

34:11.886 --> 34:13.855
You've never been to a single
party,

34:13.888 --> 34:16.824
to a single school competition
or show.

34:16.858 --> 34:19.794
I mean, I bet you spent all of
your time in a practice room.

34:19.827 --> 34:21.529
This little 10 by 10 practice
room,

34:21.563 --> 34:23.330
doing nothing but practicing all
day

34:23.363 --> 34:25.165
and eating food delivered to
you.

34:25.198 --> 34:26.500
I mean, I'm sorry, but that's
just

34:26.534 --> 34:27.735
some unpleasant problem with
discipline.

34:27.769 --> 34:30.872
You have me all figured out,
huh?

34:30.905 --> 34:32.840
Well, you missed the part

34:32.874 --> 34:35.877
where I haven't been here all
four years.

34:35.910 --> 34:39.714
Zabov pulled strings
and got me in this year.

34:40.380 --> 34:44.786
Apparently, he felt community
college was beneath me.

34:44.819 --> 34:45.887
Yeah.

34:45.920 --> 34:50.725
Tell you what, the $30
classes weren't beneath me.

34:50.758 --> 34:52.326
Look, it's your first year

34:52.359 --> 34:54.896
at conservatory and you made the
finals.

34:54.929 --> 34:57.164
- You're gonna win.
- Huh.

34:57.197 --> 35:00.668
Well, I guess if having
no life is winning.

35:01.569 --> 35:05.840
So I was right, all of
your time in a practice.

35:10.377 --> 35:11.646
I have to win.

35:13.347 --> 35:14.281
"I have to win."

35:14.314 --> 35:18.118
You'd think piano cured
cancer or something.

35:20.521 --> 35:22.690
You wouldn't understand.

35:22.724 --> 35:24.792
It's all anyone talks about.

35:24.826 --> 35:28.195
There's more to life than music.

35:28.228 --> 35:30.565
Says the girl
with the musical family.

35:30.598 --> 35:33.801
I wish my family understood what
I did.

35:34.501 --> 35:38.706
And you know, they try
to, but really I'm alone.

35:41.341 --> 35:44.545
I'm alone at home, I'm alone in
school.

35:45.980 --> 35:49.383
So my grandma's having
a birthday party tonight.

35:49.416 --> 35:50.417
- Wanna come?
- The one

35:50.450 --> 35:51.619
who's dating Zabov?

35:51.653 --> 35:53.955
- Ah, no, thank you.
- Ew, no.

35:53.988 --> 35:55.657
And that was a million years
ago.

35:55.690 --> 35:59.627
I can't, I have been
out too long as it is.

35:59.661 --> 36:01.729
I think you'd really like her.

36:01.763 --> 36:05.332
Sounds fun, but you know,
discipline.

36:05.365 --> 36:07.669
Yeah, yeah, Zoolander.

36:07.702 --> 36:12.740
Listen, if you're not ready by
now, you will never be ready.

36:12.774 --> 36:16.309
Okay, we've wasted enough time,
let's go.

36:17.512 --> 36:19.179
- What's this?
- Whoa.

36:20.014 --> 36:22.583
"The Art of Ted Urban Grand
Opening,

36:22.617 --> 36:26.353
200, Josh, hope to see
you there, Love Dad."

36:28.422 --> 36:29.590
Whatever.

36:31.859 --> 36:33.728
Back to school, right?

36:38.298 --> 36:41.536
Oh, just one more stop on the
way, okay?

36:45.472 --> 36:47.842
- Where are we?
- Oh, here, here.

36:47.875 --> 36:48.943
- Stop, stop, stop.
- Here?

36:48.976 --> 36:51.411
Yeah, yeah, good.

36:51.445 --> 36:52.847
You're crazy, there's no one
here.

36:52.880 --> 36:55.415
- Gotta see this place.
- Why?

36:56.483 --> 36:57.317
And wouldn't it be better

36:57.350 --> 37:01.022
to come back when it's opened or
never?

37:01.055 --> 37:01.923
Scared?

37:02.724 --> 37:04.692
Yeah, I'm scared of being a
black guy

37:04.726 --> 37:05.960
caught breaking into buildings.

37:05.993 --> 37:09.731
What are you doing?

37:09.764 --> 37:12.834
No breaking, just entering.

37:17.638 --> 37:19.640
Watch your step.

37:19.674 --> 37:21.609
What is this death trap?

37:21.642 --> 37:23.711
Why are you whispering?

37:26.581 --> 37:28.683
This used to be a great concert
hall.

37:28.716 --> 37:32.352
All the best of the
best used to play here.

37:32.385 --> 37:34.856
Now they use it as a revival
church

37:34.889 --> 37:36.891
and not even they can fill the
seats.

37:36.924 --> 37:38.760
- Yeah, no kidding.
- Daniel should be

37:38.793 --> 37:40.695
here somewhere.

37:40.728 --> 37:42.295
Who's Daniel?

37:42.329 --> 37:43.865
He's sort of a caretaker here.

37:43.898 --> 37:47.400
Takes care of the place
and hooligans coming in.

37:47.434 --> 37:50.303
Like us.

37:50.337 --> 37:53.473
I know you're up there,
I hear you breathing.

37:53.508 --> 37:54.575
Come on guys!

37:55.810 --> 37:56.677
Daniel.

37:58.045 --> 38:01.082
Charlie, chaps, ooh, stand
back.

38:01.115 --> 38:04.552
Got bats up here, three of 'em.

38:04.585 --> 38:05.953
I brought a friend.

38:05.987 --> 38:08.623
- Oh, a friend?
- Yes.

38:08.656 --> 38:10.390
Are you a musician too?

38:10.423 --> 38:14.394
The best, he's gonna be
a famous concert pianist.

38:14.427 --> 38:16.697
A pianist, oh, you gotta see
this!

38:16.731 --> 38:18.065
Come on!

38:18.099 --> 38:19.801
Let's go.

38:19.834 --> 38:23.571
Oh, boy, the acoustics are
just perfect.

38:23.604 --> 38:25.072
It's so sweet.

38:25.106 --> 38:29.777
It's a little torn up now, but
there's plans for a remodel.

38:29.811 --> 38:31.546
It's gonna be sweet.

