You ready?

46:16.611 --> 46:18.279
This is so weird.

46:19.246 --> 46:20.114
Why?

46:21.115 --> 46:23.050
I don't know, it just is.

46:25.953 --> 46:29.456
You just haven't gotten to
know it yet.

46:29.490 --> 46:30.357
Come.

46:32.493 --> 46:33.327
Hmm, come.

47:14.068 --> 47:16.270
Are you forgetting something?

47:16.303 --> 47:17.605
Crap, grandma!

47:23.410 --> 47:26.648
- Hello, beautiful lady.
- Oh, Margerie, dear.

47:26.681 --> 47:28.650
- How are you?
- Wonderful.

47:28.683 --> 47:30.417
Happy birthday.

47:30.451 --> 47:33.287
Will you be singing for us
tonight?

47:33.320 --> 47:34.955
Excuse me, dear.

47:34.988 --> 47:36.056
Where's Charlotte?

47:36.090 --> 47:37.525
Oh, you know, she's always
late.

47:37.559 --> 47:39.026
Your husband should be here.

47:39.059 --> 47:40.027
Well, he had to wait for the
sitter.

47:40.060 --> 47:40.994
He'll be here soon.

47:41.028 --> 47:43.230
I don't
need all of this anyway.

47:43.263 --> 47:46.233
Oh, it's your birthday,
we have to celebrate you.

47:46.266 --> 47:48.168
Besides, it's some
unwritten law that we have

47:48.202 --> 47:50.971
to annoy our family members
with cake and presents.

47:51.004 --> 47:52.139
Corinna, Corinna!

47:52.172 --> 47:54.308
- Oh!
- How are you, my sweet?

47:54.341 --> 47:57.010
It is so good to see you, happy
birthday.

47:57.044 --> 48:00.582
I cannot wait to hear you
dazzle us on the keys tonight.

48:00.615 --> 48:02.416
- Uh.
- Bryn, tell her

48:04.184 --> 48:07.388
this is her night and she
can have whatever she wants.

48:07.421 --> 48:10.124
Is everything okay over here?

48:10.157 --> 48:11.992
- What he says?
- You get whatever you want.

48:13.360 --> 48:14.928
Isn't this nice?

48:14.962 --> 48:17.131
Beautiful night, great friends.

48:17.164 --> 48:19.900
Great music and no more protest.

48:58.038 --> 48:59.607
Oh, she's so old.

48:59.641 --> 49:01.543
- Grandma.
- That is so delicious.

49:01.576 --> 49:03.177
I dare you to throw it out.

49:03.210 --> 49:04.546
Someone I want you to meet.

49:04.579 --> 49:05.446
Oh!

49:06.514 --> 49:08.482
This is my friend Josh.

49:08.516 --> 49:10.618
Oh, yes, Josh the pianist.

49:10.652 --> 49:12.687
Uh, happy to meet you, ma'am.

49:12.720 --> 49:15.523
Please, ma'am is not
necessary.

49:16.390 --> 49:20.294
So you are a Victor Zabov's new
student.

49:20.327 --> 49:23.096
The next one in line for
all the accolades, yes?

49:24.298 --> 49:26.233
I'm surprised he let you out
tonight.

49:26.266 --> 49:30.237
He usually keeps very close
guard on all his musicians.

49:30.270 --> 49:33.741
Hothouse musicians, we used to
call them.

49:33.775 --> 49:37.044
So this is Charlie's idea, I
presume.

49:38.412 --> 49:40.080
Gotta hand it to the girl.

49:40.113 --> 49:41.482
She's a wily one.

49:52.827 --> 49:54.796
It's my birthday.

49:54.829 --> 49:57.799
And I want to hear my
granddaughter play.

49:57.832 --> 50:00.200
Hmm, I'm not getting up there.

50:00.234 --> 50:01.101
Why not?

50:02.336 --> 50:04.438
Okay, I'll tell you what

50:04.471 --> 50:07.274
if that bartender does a
cartwheel before she gets back

50:07.307 --> 50:10.578
to the bar, you'll get up on
that stage.

50:11.679 --> 50:13.247
Wait for it, wait for it.

50:13.280 --> 50:14.682
It's gonna happen.

50:17.685 --> 50:19.086
It did not happen, okay.

50:21.856 --> 50:23.223
I'll tell you what.

50:23.257 --> 50:24.692
Go up there, I go up there.

50:24.726 --> 50:26.393
Oh, please.

50:26.426 --> 50:31.131
The silly arguing, both of
you, you're musicians, yes?

50:31.164 --> 50:33.267
Get up on that stage and play.

50:38.138 --> 50:39.406
You know what?

50:42.877 --> 50:43.745
Push.

50:44.646 --> 50:45.513
Yeah.

50:47.214 --> 50:51.786
Bravo, oh, bravo.

50:58.560 --> 50:59.527
Come on Mr. Beethoven.

50:59.561 --> 51:02.129
Put your fingers on the
keys and wiggle them.

53:02.382 --> 53:03.250
Bravo!

53:15.797 --> 53:17.397
Yes!

53:18.132 --> 53:21.268
- Did that just happen?
- Yes, it did.

53:21.301 --> 53:24.839
That was unreal.

53:24.872 --> 53:26.941
Not too shabby, Mr. Beethoven.

53:26.974 --> 53:29.376
That's my roommate's
girlfriend calls me.

53:29.409 --> 53:31.612
She said it's 'cause I'm
a slob like Beethoven.

53:31.646 --> 53:34.347
Oh, really?

53:34.381 --> 53:37.852
You look like a young Denzel
Washington when you laugh.

53:37.885 --> 53:39.419
"We didn't land on Plymouth
Rock!

53:39.453 --> 53:40.621
Plymouth Rock landed on us!"

53:40.655 --> 53:43.490
It's Denzel.

53:43.524 --> 53:44.926
As it's Malcolm X.

53:46.694 --> 53:50.330
- Is that a movie?
- Oh, Charlotte.

53:50.363 --> 53:51.298
No, no, no.

53:53.067 --> 53:56.470
I've seen every Denzel
movie at least six times.

53:56.504 --> 53:58.438
And not just because he's hot.

54:13.888 --> 54:15.857
- I...
- What is it?

54:15.890 --> 54:16.924
I, I'm sorry.

54:16.958 --> 54:18.059
- Did I...
- No.

54:18.092 --> 54:18.893
- Should I not have?
- No.

54:18.926 --> 54:21.863
I'm not good at
this.

54:21.896 --> 54:25.066
It's me, I shouldn't
have kept you out so long.

54:25.099 --> 54:29.670
You have an important day
tomorrow and you should go.

54:29.704 --> 54:32.305
Yeah, actually, yeah.

54:32.339 --> 54:33.541
- Yeah.
- Okay, uh.

54:33.574 --> 54:34.909
- Yes.
- Um, okay.

54:36.110 --> 54:37.979
I'll just go grab a water.

54:38.012 --> 54:40.815
- Sure, yes.
- For the long bus ride home.

54:52.727 --> 54:54.095
Really been a rough night in
there.

54:54.128 --> 54:56.831
- Thank you.
- You know, heroes.

54:56.864 --> 54:59.600
Mm.

55:01.869 --> 55:04.605
Are you out here fake smoking
again?

55:11.378 --> 55:12.713
Some show, huh?

55:14.481 --> 55:17.484
Well maybe we should go
easier on her, she is only 20.

55:17.518 --> 55:19.620
Old enough to know what she's
doing.

55:19.654 --> 55:20.555
You see it, right?

55:20.588 --> 55:21.656
She's doing the same thing to
that kid.

55:21.689 --> 55:24.692
You know what, maybe this
time it'll be different.

55:24.725 --> 55:26.594
People don't change.

55:28.729 --> 55:31.498
Are you forgetting that
maybe if things hadn't happened

55:31.532 --> 55:34.467
that way we wouldn't have
happened?

55:36.037 --> 55:39.574
Another drink, we got a
sitter.

55:39.607 --> 55:41.776
Certainly that's cause for
celebration.

55:46.814 --> 55:48.149
Ah, two waters please.

55:48.182 --> 55:49.951
- You bet.
- Thank you.

55:49.984 --> 55:52.086
There he is, man of the hour.

55:53.521 --> 55:54.622
That's nice playing.

55:54.655 --> 55:55.957
Thank you, thanks.

55:55.990 --> 55:58.826
Did you ever do the
Beethoven cello sonatas?

55:58.860 --> 56:00.695
No, but I'd love to.

56:00.728 --> 56:02.163
- Mm.
- Anything else, gentlemen?

56:02.196 --> 56:03.831
- No, we're okay.
- What are we drinking?

56:03.865 --> 56:06.000
Yours truly did

56:06.033 --> 56:08.569
many years ago at the
conservatory.

56:08.603 --> 56:11.038
My accompanist was just a kid.

56:11.072 --> 56:12.405
What was that like?

56:12.439 --> 56:13.674
Humiliating!

56:15.877 --> 56:17.945
Aren't you gonna ask me why?

56:17.979 --> 56:19.046
- Uh.
- We just started the first

56:19.080 --> 56:20.948
movement and she took off like a
bat out

56:20.982 --> 56:23.017
of hell, Just ramrodded
through the whole thing.

56:23.050 --> 56:24.619
Just pure ego.

56:24.652 --> 56:26.587
She was a real piece of work,
that one.

56:26.621 --> 56:28.589
I got slammed by the papers, but
the kid,

56:28.623 --> 56:30.892
she gets rave reviews, they
loved her.

56:30.925 --> 56:33.895
They just can't wait to
see your next appearance.

56:33.928 --> 56:35.529
She was just a kid, right?

56:35.563 --> 56:37.865
I'm sure she didn't mean
to, you know, sabotage...

56:37.899 --> 56:39.432
Just watch yourself.

56:39.466 --> 56:41.836
And what you see is not what you
get.

56:41.869 --> 56:43.704
We will have no crying in our
beers

56:43.738 --> 56:45.973
- at this party, thank you.
- Mm.

56:46.007 --> 56:48.676
Oh, and they just put out
scallops wrapped in bacon.

56:48.709 --> 56:51.579
Speaking my language.

56:51.612 --> 56:54.081
Here is to Beethoven ala bacon.

56:56.751 --> 56:59.020
Mm, this vodka's gone bad.

56:59.053 --> 57:03.524
Taste like water.

57:03.557 --> 57:05.726
Uh, yeah, excuse him.

57:05.760 --> 57:06.961
Yeah, it's okay.

57:06.994 --> 57:10.231
Um, nice performance earlier.

57:10.264 --> 57:13.601
I didn't expect that, I thought
you were strictly classical.

57:13.634 --> 57:16.570
Well, tonight's been
different.

57:16.604 --> 57:18.773
This whole day has.

57:18.806 --> 57:20.207
Are your parents coming?

57:20.241 --> 57:23.144
I'd love to meet the
people who raised that one.

57:23.177 --> 57:25.546
Oh, I'm sorry, did I say
something wrong?

57:25.579 --> 57:27.515
No, no, it's okay.

57:27.548 --> 57:29.951
Um, they're no longer with us.

57:30.985 --> 57:32.853
There was a car accident.

57:32.887 --> 57:36.489
I don't think Charlie even
remembers them.

57:36.524 --> 57:38.693
She never talks about them.

57:39.927 --> 57:40.928
I'm sorry.

57:42.596 --> 57:45.533
Now she's the only one
who ever really got Charlie.

57:45.566 --> 57:47.702
- Your grandmother?
- Yeah.

57:48.769 --> 57:49.870
I mean, when Mom and Dad passed,

57:49.904 --> 57:51.539
I was already pretty much out

57:51.572 --> 57:53.908
of the house and Charlie
was still a toddler.

57:53.941 --> 57:55.643
Well that explains the accent.

57:55.676 --> 57:56.978
Oh, yeah.

57:57.011 --> 57:59.146
Well, and Grandma raised
Charlie,

57:59.180 --> 58:01.048
but I think she picked up the
accent

58:01.082 --> 58:03.584
on purpose to be closer to her.

58:03.617 --> 58:05.219
She's pretty great.

58:07.321 --> 58:08.589
On the piano.

58:09.590 --> 58:11.192
On the piano, yeah.

58:12.927 --> 58:14.628
Look, Josh, I know it's none

58:14.662 --> 58:17.131
of my business, but
that London competition.

58:17.164 --> 58:18.632
Uh, don't remind me.

58:18.666 --> 58:20.267
My teacher would yank
me from the competition

58:20.301 --> 58:22.770
- if he knew I was here.
- So you do know that...

58:22.803 --> 58:24.572
- No, ooh, hi.
- Mm.

58:24.605 --> 58:25.773
- Hi.
- Hi.

58:25.806 --> 58:27.808
Okay, well we'll talk later.

58:27.842 --> 58:28.976
- Okay.
- Come, you.

58:29.010 --> 58:30.711
- All right.
- Let's, let's, let's...

58:30.745 --> 58:31.912
He's a good guy.

58:31.946 --> 58:33.914
Hello everyone, hi, um...

58:33.948 --> 58:34.882
Can I get two more
waters, please, sorry.

58:34.915 --> 58:37.284
I would like to thank
our guest of honor.

58:37.318 --> 58:38.953
And thank you all for coming.

58:38.986 --> 58:41.155
Our guest of honor is Grandma
Corinna.

58:44.725 --> 58:47.294
I think as a thank you gift for
us,

58:47.328 --> 58:50.765
for her birthday, she should
sing us or play us something.

58:50.798 --> 58:52.166
- Yes!
- Yes, yes!

58:52.199 --> 58:54.201
Yes!

58:54.235 --> 58:57.304
Those among the crowd,
come on, some cheering!

58:57.338 --> 59:00.975
Yes, yes, yes!

59:01.008 --> 59:02.543
Come on, come on!

59:31.705 --> 59:36.710
♪ As the wind strips the trees
bare ♪

59:37.546 --> 59:42.750
♪ Dogwood blooms float here and
there ♪

59:43.918 --> 59:48.189
♪ On the path where you declared ♪

59:48.222 --> 59:53.227
♪ How much you care ♪

59:54.195 --> 59:59.600
♪ Are you gone like the petals
in he air ♪

1:00:05.439 --> 1:00:10.644
♪ As the steam would drift on
the lake ♪

1:00:11.278 --> 1:00:16.283
♪ I would dream of hours we
would make ♪

1:00:17.718 --> 1:00:22.156
♪ On the day when we declared ♪

1:00:22.189 --> 1:00:27.161
♪ A love we shared ♪

1:00:28.062 --> 1:00:33.267
♪ While our guests scattered
petals in the air ♪

1:00:53.320 --> 1:00:54.321
Thank you.

1:00:56.490 --> 1:00:59.126
I must know a hundred melodies,

1:01:00.828 --> 1:01:04.064
but the last few years I've been
playing

1:01:04.098 --> 1:01:06.367
the same ones over and over.

1:01:07.134 --> 1:01:12.239
I sit at the piano and it's
the same melodies all the time.

1:01:12.273 --> 1:01:13.874
I don't know if I was trying

1:01:13.908 --> 1:01:17.912
to perfect them or if I'm
just a creature of habit,

1:01:17.945 --> 1:01:21.415
but then my hands couldn't
stretch as far.

1:01:22.950 --> 1:01:26.687
And then it became
difficult to play at all.

1:01:27.922 --> 1:01:31.125
And it's hard to admit
that even here on my,

1:01:31.158 --> 1:01:35.029
hmm, birthday.

1:01:35.062 --> 1:01:39.500
When you love something
and then one day it's gone,

1:01:39.534 --> 1:01:44.205
you realize that maybe
it's good that you decided

1:01:44.238 --> 1:01:48.976
to have a life outside the
music, but I have no regrets.

1:01:50.311 --> 1:01:51.979
I have lived fully.

1:01:53.113 --> 1:01:55.049
And I have loved fully.

1:01:56.217 --> 1:02:01.422
And now my Charlie is going
to take over in my footsteps

1:02:01.822 --> 1:02:04.491
and make her grandma so proud.

1:02:05.527 --> 1:02:09.163
Congratulations to
Charlotte and wish her well

1:02:09.196 --> 1:02:11.932
for her big competition
tomorrow.

1:02:19.273 --> 1:02:20.774
I thought you left
without saying goodbye.

1:02:20.808 --> 1:02:22.009
Why is he here?

1:02:22.042 --> 1:02:23.377
I think it's because of
grandma.

1:02:23.410 --> 1:02:24.979
No, no, you said they weren't
a thing.

1:02:25.012 --> 1:02:27.181
- They're not.
- Okay, I have to leave

1:02:27.214 --> 1:02:29.216
before he sees me here,
but my bag is inside,

1:02:29.250 --> 1:02:33.220
my bike is out front,
what am I supposed...

1:02:33.254 --> 1:02:34.355
There's something else.

1:02:34.388 --> 1:02:36.090
What, what else?

1:02:36.123 --> 1:02:37.491
Josh, I need to tell you
something.

1:02:37.525 --> 1:02:40.127
What, what, Charlotte, what?

1:02:41.462 --> 1:02:43.964
There you are, missy.

1:02:43.998 --> 1:02:48.202
I don't appreciate you
forcing me up on that stage.

1:02:48.235 --> 1:02:49.803
And you, where are you
off to in such a hurry?

1:02:49.837 --> 1:02:50.904
I have to go.

1:02:50.938 --> 1:02:51.772
Zabov is gonna pull me

1:02:51.805 --> 1:02:54.041
from the competition if he sees
me here.

1:02:54.074 --> 1:02:56.343
That's absolutely correct.

1:02:57.878 --> 1:03:00.881
Victor Zabov, nothing has
changed.

1:03:01.583 --> 1:03:03.884
You're still an ass.

1:03:03.917 --> 1:03:05.819
That's crass, Corinna.

1:03:05.853 --> 1:03:07.988
If you don't let your
musicians live a little,

1:03:08.022 --> 1:03:10.357
how are they going to bring
any life into their music?

1:03:10.391 --> 1:03:12.092
He's a good teacher,
Corinna, he's just trying-

1:03:12.126 --> 1:03:14.161
- I can handle my own battles,
Josh.

1:03:14.194 --> 1:03:17.599
Oh, you said something he
has always been able to handle.

1:03:17.632 --> 1:03:18.600
His battles.

1:03:18.633 --> 1:03:21.835
Let me take you home,
I have a car waiting.

1:03:21.869 --> 1:03:23.037
Why?

1:03:23.070 --> 1:03:25.472
So you can lock me in a room
like you do your musicians?

1:03:25.507 --> 1:03:27.408
Not letting them live their
lives.

1:03:27.441 --> 1:03:29.476
I do that for their own good.

1:03:29.511 --> 1:03:31.312
Joshua wouldn't have gotten this
far,

1:03:31.345 --> 1:03:34.014
if it wasn't for strict
discipline.

1:03:34.048 --> 1:03:36.584
And now he's playing
for one of the greatest

1:03:36.618 --> 1:03:39.386
- competitions in the-
- Oh, posh!

1:03:39.420 --> 1:03:41.455
It doesn't matter who you're
playing for

1:03:41.488 --> 1:03:43.023
or what you're playing.

1:03:43.057 --> 1:03:46.260
A musician has to connect
with his audience.

1:03:46.293 --> 1:03:49.096
I don't care if you play
every single note perfectly.

1:03:49.129 --> 1:03:53.200
If you don't have anything
to say, don't waste my time.

1:03:53.233 --> 1:03:56.236
And you, what you did in there
tonight,

1:03:56.270 --> 1:03:59.006
now that was something special.

1:04:00.107 --> 1:04:01.442
- Oh, oh!
- Grandma!

1:04:02.309 --> 1:04:05.913
Corinna, are you all right?

1:04:05.946 --> 1:04:07.549
I told you I was gonna take you
home.

1:04:07.582 --> 1:04:08.916
Now I'll take you to the
hospital.

1:04:08.949 --> 1:04:12.086
Lift her up.

1:04:12.119 --> 1:04:15.489
- Josh, grab my purse.
- Hold her, hold her.

1:04:15.523 --> 1:04:17.458
Come on, go ahead, go.

1:04:17.491 --> 1:04:18.425
Go, go, go.

1:04:21.195 --> 1:04:23.263
Amy is sound asleep.

1:04:23.297 --> 1:04:25.899
I don't think she missed us one
bit.

1:04:25.933 --> 1:04:28.135
Gosh, seeing those kids tonight

1:04:28.168 --> 1:04:30.137
reminded me of how I used to be
with us.

1:04:30.170 --> 1:04:31.271
When was the last time we were
all goofy

1:04:31.305 --> 1:04:33.173
and playful like that?

1:04:34.509 --> 1:04:35.376
Baby, hey,

1:04:37.679 --> 1:04:39.547
it happened, it's over.

1:04:39.581 --> 1:04:42.449
Besides, she's not the reason
you stopped playing, remember?

1:04:42.483 --> 1:04:44.451
Come on, why did you stop
playing?

1:04:44.485 --> 1:04:46.153
Because I quit auditioning.

1:04:46.186 --> 1:04:47.054
Why?

1:04:48.021 --> 1:04:50.991
'Cause that curmudgeon
conductor said my bow work

1:04:51.024 --> 1:04:52.527
looked like a hippo with
arthritis.

1:04:52.560 --> 1:04:54.228
Oh, come on, why?

1:04:55.496 --> 1:04:57.364
'Cause I was losing my soul.

1:04:57.398 --> 1:05:00.000
And it became about winning.

1:05:11.679 --> 1:05:13.447
Do you regret our life together?

1:05:13.480 --> 1:05:14.415
What, no.

1:05:16.250 --> 1:05:17.985
No, I love our life.

1:05:20.254 --> 1:05:21.321
You're right.

1:05:27.294 --> 1:05:28.228
I love you.

1:05:34.268 --> 1:05:37.705
Remember when it used to be
fun?

1:05:37.739 --> 1:05:39.507
No!

1:05:39.541 --> 1:05:40.708
Yes, come on, play with me.

1:05:40.742 --> 1:05:42.476
- No!
- Come on!

1:05:42.510 --> 1:05:44.478
- No, no, no.
- Come on.

1:05:44.512 --> 1:05:47.114
No, no, please, turn it off.

1:05:48.115 --> 1:05:49.183
No.

1:05:49.216 --> 1:05:50.951
- Play with me.
- No.

1:05:52.419 --> 1:05:53.688
♪ Some days it seems ♪

1:05:53.721 --> 1:05:56.089
♪ We can't agree ♪

1:05:56.123 --> 1:05:59.594
♪ And our duet's gone out of key ♪

1:05:59.627 --> 1:06:04.031
♪ I wonder if this love's passe ♪

1:06:04.064 --> 1:06:06.768
Mm.

1:06:06.801 --> 1:06:10.337
♪ But then you croon a note or
two ♪

1:06:10.370 --> 1:06:14.041
♪ And soon my will to fight is
through ♪

1:06:14.074 --> 1:06:19.079
♪ You sing my doubts and fears
away ♪

1:06:21.181 --> 1:06:24.619
♪ Your smooth vivacious voice ♪

1:06:24.652 --> 1:06:28.355
♪ Leaves me without a choice ♪

1:06:28.388 --> 1:06:33.494
♪ And drives you right back to
my arms ♪

1:06:35.462 --> 1:06:38.232
♪ You're like a tidal wave ♪

1:06:38.265 --> 1:06:41.603
♪ That washes me along ♪

1:06:41.636 --> 1:06:46.641
♪ I'm a prisoner of your siren
song ♪

1:06:51.345 --> 1:06:56.183
♪ Yes your siren song ♪

1:07:13.400 --> 1:07:16.103
Don't be silly, I'm not dying.

1:07:17.639 --> 1:07:19.574
Let's get you to bed.

1:07:21.108 --> 1:07:22.744
I still think she should see a
doctor.

1:07:22.777 --> 1:07:24.478
She needs an x-ray.

1:07:24.512 --> 1:07:26.179
I'll call first thing in
morning.

1:07:26.213 --> 1:07:28.348
Stop, all of you!

1:07:28.382 --> 1:07:31.218
Can't an old woman have some
peace?

1:08:03.651 --> 1:08:05.787
So last time something
like this happened,

1:08:05.820 --> 1:08:09.289
the doctor said it might
have been a mini-stroke.

1:08:09.323 --> 1:08:10.424
He said it could come up again

1:08:10.457 --> 1:08:14.261
with no warning, but she
keeps saying this was nothing.

1:08:14.294 --> 1:08:16.296
She'll go to the doctor
tomorrow

1:08:16.330 --> 1:08:18.666
if I have to take her myself.

1:08:19.701 --> 1:08:21.101
Stubborn woman.

1:08:21.936 --> 1:08:26.541
What I want to know is what's
going on between you two?

1:08:26.574 --> 1:08:29.376
Don't you care for your
careers, your music?

1:08:29.409 --> 1:08:30.545
I have been studying non-stop.

1:08:30.578 --> 1:08:31.679
- I convinced him to go.
- For four weeks.

1:08:31.713 --> 1:08:32.547
- It wasn't even his idea.
- This is the first night

1:08:32.580 --> 1:08:33.380
- I left, okay?
- And he was practicing.

1:08:33.413 --> 1:08:34.048
- I'm sorry.
- And I was helping him.

1:08:34.082 --> 1:08:36.784
- I messed up.
- Silence!

1:08:38.385 --> 1:08:40.387
Josh, I am disappointed.

1:08:42.356 --> 1:08:44.324
You actually had what it takes
to win.

1:08:44.358 --> 1:08:47.494
And then you go and do
something stupid like this.

1:08:47.528 --> 1:08:48.696
Did you really think the way

1:08:48.730 --> 1:08:52.332
to win was to sabotage another
competitor?

1:08:53.433 --> 1:08:54.468
Wait, what?

1:08:54.501 --> 1:08:57.437
If you just worked as
hard seated at your piano

1:08:57.471 --> 1:08:59.306
as you do distracting Josh,

1:08:59.339 --> 1:09:01.909
you'd have been the sure winner.

1:09:01.943 --> 1:09:04.545
And you, after our talk today,

1:09:05.580 --> 1:09:08.950
I don't understand this
behavior.

1:09:08.983 --> 1:09:13.521
I put too much faith in
you.

1:09:16.557 --> 1:09:18.291
Now go, both of you.

1:09:19.727 --> 1:09:21.194
Get out of here!

1:09:26.266 --> 1:09:28.468
I'll stay here for Corinna.

1:09:37.979 --> 1:09:40.515
Why won't you unlock?

1:09:40.548 --> 1:09:42.650
Josh, please, I wanted to tell
you.

1:09:42.684 --> 1:09:43.785
I tried to tell you.

1:09:43.818 --> 1:09:46.921
When, like when did you
try to tell me, Charlotte?

1:09:46.954 --> 1:09:48.156
When you, when you made me think
that

1:09:48.188 --> 1:09:50.625
I was somehow special and you
wanted to hang out with me?

1:09:50.658 --> 1:09:52.259
When you, when you used me

1:09:52.292 --> 1:09:53.260
as your escort around town all
day?

1:09:53.293 --> 1:09:54.762
- Like when?
- You can still win.

1:09:54.796 --> 1:09:57.732
Oh my God, how long have
you been in the competition?

1:09:57.765 --> 1:09:58.900
And you're one of the finalists?

1:09:58.933 --> 1:10:00.300
Josh, please, you can still
win.

1:10:00.333 --> 1:10:01.969
So was that your plan all
along?

1:10:02.003 --> 1:10:03.503
To, to distract me, right?

1:10:03.538 --> 1:10:06.473
Like throw me off my game.

1:10:06.507 --> 1:10:08.308
- Was that your plan?
- Yes.

1:10:08.341 --> 1:10:09.944
- Yes, at first, but-
- And the girl Milo

1:10:09.977 --> 1:10:14.281
told me about that stole
his moment, that was you.

1:10:14.314 --> 1:10:15.282
I didn't want to believe it,

1:10:15.315 --> 1:10:17.317
that this girl that I...

1:10:19.419 --> 1:10:20.220
- That you what?
- Forget...

1:10:20.253 --> 1:10:22.289
- What, Josh?
- It doesn't matter.

1:10:22.322 --> 1:10:23.725
Okay, not anymore.

1:10:24.525 --> 1:10:27.829
Dammit, Charlotte, you put
my entire life in jeopardy.

1:10:27.862 --> 1:10:29.463
Everything I've worked for!

1:10:29.496 --> 1:10:31.599
Runner-up gets nothing, okay?

1:10:31.632 --> 1:10:33.868
If I don't win this, then all
the lessons,

1:10:33.901 --> 1:10:35.670
all the money that my mom put

1:10:35.703 --> 1:10:37.638
in to pay for those lessons, for
nothing!

1:10:37.672 --> 1:10:40.007
Because it isn't about
winning.

1:10:40.041 --> 1:10:42.476
Do you really
wanna go there right now?

1:10:42.510 --> 1:10:44.011
I'm sorry, it's just,

1:10:44.045 --> 1:10:46.480
everyone was talking about how
perfect

1:10:46.514 --> 1:10:49.282
your technique was, how you
were everyone's favorite.

1:10:49.316 --> 1:10:52.319
Because I spend my
life in a practice room!

1:10:52.352 --> 1:10:54.956
I have done nothing but
work to get to this moment!

1:10:54.989 --> 1:10:57.992
You could have done the
same thing instead of...

1:10:58.025 --> 1:11:01.361
You couldn't even tell me
you were in the finals.

1:11:01.394 --> 1:11:05.398
Do you really think that
would have changed anything?

1:11:05.432 --> 1:11:06.834
Maybe, I just...

1:11:07.835 --> 1:11:09.369
- Josh, please.
- Stop, stop it!

1:11:09.402 --> 1:11:11.873
Charlotte, just leave me alone.

1:11:12.807 --> 1:11:15.042
Okay, this day was a mistake.

1:11:15.076 --> 1:11:18.946
My life, my plans,
everything's all jacked up!

1:11:20.815 --> 1:11:22.016
You have no idea what it's like

1:11:22.049 --> 1:11:23.751
for me here at this white-ass
school!

1:11:23.785 --> 1:11:26.721
You think people are clamoring
to hire people like me?

1:11:26.754 --> 1:11:28.589
People like you, but you're so
talented.

1:11:28.623 --> 1:11:31.458
I can't make a single mistake.

1:11:31.491 --> 1:11:33.995
Not one, you have no
idea what that's like.

1:11:34.028 --> 1:11:35.395
Yes, I do, I'm a woman.

1:11:35.428 --> 1:11:37.064
It's not the same!

1:11:37.098 --> 1:11:39.066
Like you saying that just proves

1:11:39.100 --> 1:11:40.101
you don't know what you're
talking about.

1:11:40.134 --> 1:11:41.869
You just, you just coast
through,

1:11:41.903 --> 1:11:43.738
not taking anything seriously,
just...

1:11:43.771 --> 1:11:46.007
And somehow you got into the
finals

1:11:46.040 --> 1:11:48.441
of one of the most prestigious
competitions in the worst!

1:11:48.475 --> 1:11:51.411
Why is everyone making
such a big deal out of it?

1:11:51.444 --> 1:11:53.614
Everyone's gonna know who's
Beethoven in a hundred years,

1:11:53.648 --> 1:11:57.018
will they know who Josh Irving
is?

1:11:57.051 --> 1:11:59.554
Oh, shit, Josh, I didn't
mean it like that.

1:11:59.587 --> 1:12:00.453
Josh!

1:12:01.122 --> 1:12:03.057
No, I'm sorry, I meant all of
us.

1:12:03.090 --> 1:12:07.360
You are not the person
I thought you were.

1:12:07.394 --> 1:12:08.796
Neither are you.

1:12:11.398 --> 1:12:13.801
You act like everyone is
abandoning you,

1:12:13.835 --> 1:12:15.703
but you're the one who choose
all of this.

1:12:15.736 --> 1:12:18.139
You choose to spend your
life in a practice room.

1:12:18.172 --> 1:12:20.541
You choose to think that
you're somehow different

1:12:20.575 --> 1:12:21.843
so you couldn't have any
friends.

1:12:21.876 --> 1:12:23.410
And you choose to think

1:12:23.443 --> 1:12:25.813
that you have to be
perfect to have a career.

1:12:25.847 --> 1:12:27.715
I don't know what the
thing with your father is,

1:12:27.748 --> 1:12:29.884
but at least you have one.

1:12:33.588 --> 1:12:36.924
- What about your bike?
- I'll take the bus!

1:14:19.527 --> 1:14:22.196
I'd never seen her happier,
hmm.

1:14:23.597 --> 1:14:25.933
Mm, you were her whole world.

1:14:27.001 --> 1:14:28.803
You were the light of her life,
man.

1:14:28.836 --> 1:14:32.840
After you were born, she
didn't need anything.

1:14:32.873 --> 1:14:34.608
Not her art, not me.

1:14:37.211 --> 1:14:40.982
You were hardly
there.

1:14:41.015 --> 1:14:43.684
You don't know what she needed.

1:14:45.286 --> 1:14:47.487
I know, and I'm sorry.

1:14:53.227 --> 1:14:55.563
You know, this photograph,

1:14:56.230 --> 1:15:00.968
this photograph is the thing
that got me painting again.

1:15:02.036 --> 1:15:03.871
Deepened my love for art.

1:15:03.904 --> 1:15:06.073
Your mom and I had just come
from a little flea market

1:15:06.107 --> 1:15:09.110
and I bought her a used
Roller-flex.

1:15:10.044 --> 1:15:12.113
And I snapped that on the fly.

1:15:12.146 --> 1:15:15.783
And later that night, she told
me she was pregnant with you.

1:15:15.816 --> 1:15:17.284
Why are you here?

1:15:19.220 --> 1:15:22.823
Why are you suddenly hellbound
on staying?

1:15:23.657 --> 1:15:27.061
I had an opportunity, I had to
leave.

1:15:27.995 --> 1:15:30.664
I'm not saying it's right,

1:15:30.698 --> 1:15:32.767
but it was what I felt I had to
do.

1:15:34.335 --> 1:15:37.238
But looking back, all the
traveling, all the places,

1:15:37.271 --> 1:15:39.573
all the running around, trying
to get the perfect shot,

1:15:39.607 --> 1:15:40.474
the perfect sunset.

1:15:40.509 --> 1:15:43.577
I would trade all that in a
heartbeat

1:15:43.611 --> 1:15:47.715
to get back the moments I
lost with you and your mom.

1:15:47.748 --> 1:15:50.751
I didn't know it then, but I do
now.

1:15:52.053 --> 1:15:54.255
And I'm gonna prove it to you.

1:15:54.288 --> 1:15:56.090
Like tonight, this competition,

1:15:56.123 --> 1:15:59.860
whatever happens, I'm
gonna be here for you.

1:16:00.795 --> 1:16:03.330
If moving mom away, is what you

1:16:06.200 --> 1:16:09.904
and she wants, then
I'll go wherever you go,

1:16:13.207 --> 1:16:16.744
'cause it's not about where I am
anymore,

1:16:18.145 --> 1:16:19.980
about where you are.

1:16:20.014 --> 1:16:22.750
And I'm gonna prove that to you.

1:16:26.320 --> 1:16:30.357
If you knew how hard
mom worked all these years

1:16:32.960 --> 1:16:35.362
while you were out living it up.

1:16:35.396 --> 1:16:37.898
All pompous with your travel log
photos

1:16:37.932 --> 1:16:40.334
and drinking wine with
these pretentious idiots

1:16:40.367 --> 1:16:43.904
who think you're some kind of
genius!

1:16:43.938 --> 1:16:47.007
And then you come here and
pretend

1:16:47.041 --> 1:16:51.745
to be interested in what I'm
doing every couple of years.

1:16:51.779 --> 1:16:54.315
You have no idea what it's like.

1:16:55.816 --> 1:16:57.651
You don't care about me

1:16:57.685 --> 1:17:01.255
or my music or about my goals
to move mom away from here.

1:17:01.288 --> 1:17:02.957
It's all about you!

1:17:06.894 --> 1:17:08.062
Still.

1:17:18.973 --> 1:17:22.309
Hey grandma, shouldn't
you be at the doctors?

1:17:22.343 --> 1:17:24.145
I'm back, I'm fine.

1:17:26.080 --> 1:17:27.014
I told you.

1:17:29.016 --> 1:17:30.184
Where is Zabov?

1:17:30.217 --> 1:17:33.420
He went to buy
some groceries to make lunch.

1:17:33.454 --> 1:17:35.122
Stubborn old fool.

1:17:39.326 --> 1:17:40.427
What you did last night-

1:17:40.461 --> 1:17:42.263
- I know, I'm sorry.

1:17:45.766 --> 1:17:47.835
What you did was wrong.

1:17:48.903 --> 1:17:51.338
You're better than that.

1:17:51.372 --> 1:17:53.240
But I take some fault.

1:17:55.042 --> 1:17:56.944
I pressed you too hard to win.

1:17:56.977 --> 1:17:58.445
No, Grandma, it's not...

1:17:58.479 --> 1:18:01.815
I forgot what it's like to be
young.

1:18:03.117 --> 1:18:06.820
Have a life of opportunity
in front of you.

1:18:06.854 --> 1:18:08.155
In love.

1:18:08.189 --> 1:18:09.990
I'm not in love.

1:18:10.024 --> 1:18:11.058
You are so head over heels,

1:18:11.091 --> 1:18:14.728
you can't walk unless
you're doing a handstand.

1:18:14.762 --> 1:18:16.764
I was so worried about your
future.

1:18:16.797 --> 1:18:19.466
I could only see that
competition.

1:18:20.569 --> 1:18:25.839
It was the love of the music,
not the fame, not the money.

1:18:26.874 --> 1:18:28.876
It was always the music.

1:18:29.944 --> 1:18:34.148
When I watched you and
Josh up there last night,

1:18:35.816 --> 1:18:40.020
a new fire got lit in this
old dusty heart of mine.

1:18:41.488 --> 1:18:44.091
Oh, I haven't felt that since-

1:18:44.959 --> 1:18:46.327
- Grandpa?

1:18:46.360 --> 1:18:47.428
No, before.

1:18:49.029 --> 1:18:52.099
Do ever regret not taking a
chance?

1:19:00.341 --> 1:19:03.010
I'll meet you in the kitchen.

1:19:10.351 --> 1:19:15.022
Sometimes, but then I wouldn't
have you or your sister.

1:19:23.831 --> 1:19:27.001
You have to figure out
what it is you want,

1:19:27.034 --> 1:19:29.336
not what the rest of us want.

1:19:29.370 --> 1:19:32.574
Everyone is just trying to
figure out their own shit.

1:19:32.607 --> 1:19:33.474
Grandma!

1:19:34.875 --> 1:19:38.412
Yes, your grandma
curses on occasion too.

1:19:38.445 --> 1:19:40.515
Practice, don't practice.

1:19:41.282 --> 1:19:44.151
I'm going to get myself some
lunch.

1:20:00.301 --> 1:20:02.036
I would've stayed.

1:20:03.370 --> 1:20:04.238
I know.

1:20:05.906 --> 1:20:07.308
That's why I left.

1:20:15.650 --> 1:20:17.217
Hey, package for Josh Irving.

1:20:17.251 --> 1:20:19.486
- Yeah, that's me.
- All right.

1:20:19.521 --> 1:20:21.455
Just sign here, please.

1:20:25.159 --> 1:20:26.427
- You have a good day.
- Thanks, you too.

1:20:26.460 --> 1:20:27.328
Okay.

1:22:23.678 --> 1:22:26.548
You, I saw you at the piano
bar.

1:22:27.715 --> 1:22:30.017
That was magnificent, young man.

1:22:30.050 --> 1:22:31.218
The caliber of your talent is
gonna

1:22:31.251 --> 1:22:33.454
put you on the world stage.

1:22:35.122 --> 1:22:37.090
I look forward to what your
future holds.

1:22:37.124 --> 1:22:40.394
And look at that face, the full
package.

1:22:40.427 --> 1:22:41.295
Fabulous.

1:22:43.430 --> 1:22:44.566
You're ready.

1:22:44.599 --> 1:22:46.133
You're ready.

1:22:46.166 --> 1:22:47.167
Confidence.

1:22:48.603 --> 1:22:51.071
Saturday is gone, take a deep
breath.

1:22:52.707 --> 1:22:54.408
Deep breaths.

1:22:54.441 --> 1:22:58.045
Now, once you perform, you
come backstage and wait.

1:22:58.078 --> 1:23:00.013
The results will be announced
immediately

1:23:00.047 --> 1:23:02.015
following the competition.

1:23:02.049 --> 1:23:03.984
So Beatrice, you're up.

1:23:08.255 --> 1:23:10.457
- Good luck.
- Thanks.

1:23:10.491 --> 1:23:12.059
You too.

1:23:21.836 --> 1:23:26.373
I'm glad to see you've
come to your senses.

1:23:26.406 --> 1:23:29.544
Potassium for the nerves,
smart boy.

1:23:31.813 --> 1:23:33.781
- Victor.
- Corinna.

1:23:33.815 --> 1:23:34.682
Hmm.

1:23:36.250 --> 1:23:39.621
I just wanted to tell
you good luck tonight.

1:23:39.654 --> 1:23:41.823
You are a stellar pianist.

1:23:41.856 --> 1:23:45.325
And just remember, play from
your heart.

1:23:46.326 --> 1:23:47.194
Hmm?

1:23:48.796 --> 1:23:51.633
- May I help you off?
- Certainly.

1:24:04.177 --> 1:24:06.179
Why do you play, Josh?

1:24:07.414 --> 1:24:08.616
I, because...

1:24:10.217 --> 1:24:11.285
'Cause why?

1:24:12.185 --> 1:24:14.187
Do you love it?

1:24:14.221 --> 1:24:17.224
I've taught you everything I
can.

1:24:17.257 --> 1:24:20.193
Now it's up to you to
do what's in your heart.

1:24:20.227 --> 1:24:22.129
Trust your instincts.

1:24:22.162 --> 1:24:24.264
Don't let any moment get away.

1:26:53.948 --> 1:26:56.751
Now that we got that over
with.

1:27:00.588 --> 1:27:01.989
Once upon a time,

1:27:03.991 --> 1:27:07.829
a young Beethoven got
to play for his idol,

1:27:07.862 --> 1:27:09.564
Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart,

1:27:09.597 --> 1:27:13.634
in the hope that he would
get to study under him.

1:27:15.069 --> 1:27:18.940
Uh, the story goes that
Mozart had no interest

1:27:19.741 --> 1:27:22.677
in being interrupted by
something

1:27:22.710 --> 1:27:25.445
so frivolous and was even colder

1:27:26.514 --> 1:27:30.852
when Beethoven played a
studied piece of Mozart's.

1:27:33.020 --> 1:27:36.624
Beethoven begged for another
chance.

1:27:36.657 --> 1:27:40.427
Mozart played a tune
that the young composer

1:27:40.460 --> 1:27:42.530
could never have possibly heard.

1:27:42.563 --> 1:27:46.500
Beethoven then went on to
improvise on that tune.

1:27:46.534 --> 1:27:49.737
Rumor has it that after
Beethoven played,

1:27:49.771 --> 1:27:52.774
Mozart said, "Look out for that
boy.

1:27:53.808 --> 1:27:56.811
One day he'll give the world
something to talk about."

1:27:56.844 --> 1:27:59.847
Beethoven never went on
to study under Mozart,

1:27:59.881 --> 1:28:04.752
but he became beloved all on
his own, doing his own thing.

1:28:08.723 --> 1:28:10.858
Now, if you'll indulge me,

1:28:14.361 --> 1:28:16.597
I'd like to try my own thing,

1:28:16.631 --> 1:28:18.699
inspired by Beethoven and

1:28:22.737 --> 1:28:24.337
a few new friends.

1:28:28.543 --> 1:28:29.811
For you tonight.

1:30:37.071 --> 1:30:40.473
Sorry, Grandma, my heart's not
in it.

1:30:42.109 --> 1:30:45.179
But everything will be fine,
promise.

1:30:46.881 --> 1:30:47.815
Love you.

1:32:10.998 --> 1:32:15.703
♪ The storm has abated ♪

1:32:15.736 --> 1:32:20.174
♪ The sheep are safe to roam ♪

1:32:20.207 --> 1:32:24.211
